info.headline: Wind Advisory issued March 10 at 4:26AM PST until March 10 at 4:00PM PST by NWS Monterey
info.description: ...WIND ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 4 PM PST THIS AFTERNOON... * WHAT...South winds 15 to 25 mph with gusts up to 55 mph. * WHERE...Portions of California. * WHEN...Until 4 PM PST Friday. * IMPACTS...Gusty winds could blow around unsecured objects. Tree limbs could be blown down and a few power outages may result as soils remain very saturated. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Locally stronger wind gusts greater than 60 mph will be possible in the favored coastal areas, higher terrain and coastal gaps. Area`s with very wet soils will see a greater risk for downed trees and power lines.
info.instruction: Use extra caution when driving, especially if operating a high profile vehicle. Secure outdoor objects.
